
[1]clay-stone

   CLAY-STONE, n. A mineral, the thonstein of Werner, and indurated clay
   of Kirwan. It resembles compact limestone or calcarious marl. Its
   texture is porous, compact or slaty. Its color is gray, often tinged
   with yellow or blue; also rose or pale red, or brownish red, and
   sometimes greenish.
